<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-18T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-18T11:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/807a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Collier</hi></persName>)<note n="91" xml:id="d189fn91">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                                        mutandis</hi>, to the Chargé in Peru (no. 4).</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-18T11:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            18, 1922—11 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>4. Favorable replies having been received from both Chile and Peru,
                                you are instructed to address the Minister of Foreign Affairs in the
                                terms quoted in Department’s 2, January 13, 4 p.m. An identic
                                telegram has been sent to Lima. Report action by cable.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>